"{\"uid\": \"rollingstone.com-culture-culture-news-olympic-boxing-champion-imane-khelif-files-online-harassment-complaint-paris-1235078078\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"BySimon Vozick-Levinson  Three days ago, Algerian boxer Imane Khelifwon a gold medalin the women's welterweight division of the 2024Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It should have been a triumphant moment for an athlete who spent years training for this moment and won all four of her matches on the world's biggest stage.\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, her victory was shadowed by a relentless campaign ofbad-faith criticismfocused on factually baseless claims about hergender.\", \"from\": 300, \"to\": 433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because the games took place in France, which hasrobust lawsagainst online hate speech, Khelif has now filed a legal complaint with a Paris prosecutor's office.\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 466, \"end\": 472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9924227544267463, \"rank\": 0.006825958004653309, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 568, \"end\": 573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.4585936422545265e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to theAssociated Press, Khelif's lawyers filed the complaint alleging \\\"aggravated cyber-harassment\\\" on Aug. 9, the day she won the gold medal.\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The complaint reportedly does not name a specific perpetrator; instead, the prosecutor's office will conduct an investigation and decide whether to charge anyone under the statute, which could call for two to five years in prison and tens of thousands of Euros in fines.\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 1019, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Attorney Nabil Boudi wrotein the complaintthat the campaign of \\\"speculation fueled by malicious individuals\\u2026 exceeded 100 million views\\\" on the X platform, becoming an \\\"ordeal\\\" for Khelif.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I send a message to all the people of the world to uphold the Olympic principles and the Olympic Charter, to refrain from bullying all athletes, because this has effects, massive effects,\\\" Khelif reportedly told the sports video news service SNTV.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She added that online harassment \\\"can destroy people, it can kill people's thoughts, spirit and mind.\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It can divide people.\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And because of that, I ask them to refrain from bullying.\\\"\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The manufactured right-wing controversy around Khelif began on Aug. 1, when her opponent, Italian boxer Angela Carini, withdrew from a bout after just 46 seconds, saying, \\\"I have never been hit so hard in my life.\\\"\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9918651035986105, \"rank\": 0.005916156043566746, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999962103660394, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This led to a torrent of specious critiques from people like Elon Musk, J.K. Rowling, Donald Trump, and Logan Paul, all of whom falsely suggested that Khelif is a trans woman and/or that she should be barred from women's athletic events.\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 2097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1921, \"end\": 1930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.712567119041674e-23, \"text\": \"J.K.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\"}, {\"begin\": 1946, \"end\": 1958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999998992184425, \"rank\": 9.365299948823337e-08, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 1964, \"end\": 1974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Logan_Paul\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Logan Paul\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Logan_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Logan_Paul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, Khelif, 25, was raised as a girl from birth, has never identified as a man, and lives in a country with strict anti-trans laws that would make the scenario invented by conservative critics extremely unlikely.\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The allegations about her gender are simply not true.\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Paul later posteda statementthat began with the word \\\"OOPSIES,\\\" admitting that \\\"I might be guilty of spreading misinformation.\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\")Trending StoriesJohn Lithgow Knows J.K. Rowling's Anti-Trans Views Will Now Forever Come Up in 'Every Interview'Kevin Spacey's 'Mental Illness' Should Trigger $29.5 Million Payout, 'House of Cards' Trial Jurors HearBTS Nails Its Comeback With 'Arirang'Top Disaster Response Official Claims He Teleported to a Waffle HouseEditor's picksThe 250 Greatest Albums of the 21st Century So FarThe 100 Best TV Episodes of All TimeThe 500 Greatest Albums of All Time100 Best Movies of the 21st Century  While the Russian-dominated InternationalBoxingAssociation disqualified Khelif and another boxer from last year's world championships, that decision has been roundly rejected by the boxing community; the IBA is currently led by a right-wing Putin crony with ahistoryof homophobic and transphobic remarks.\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 3296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3196, \"end\": 3199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9960510200799311, \"rank\": 0.003964517677975491, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 3233, \"end\": 3238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.405405328910213e-19, \"text\": \"Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}, {\"begin\": 3261, \"end\": 3271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homophobia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.123386811324329e-13, \"text\": \"homophobic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homophobia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homophobia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International Olympic Committee President Thomas Bach has condemned the\\\"hate speech\\u2026aggression and abuse\\\"directed at Khelif, which he linked to Russia's ongoing conflict with the IOC.\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3297, \"end\": 3328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 3441, \"end\": 3447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999826259228, \"rank\": 1.0686193635162403e-08, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3476, \"end\": 3479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.282688485616088e-24, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carini, for her part, swiftly disavowed the entire line of attack being employed by her supposed supporters.\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3482, \"end\": 3488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999999994192876, \"rank\": 5.808363308171025e-10, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The day after the bout, she said she'd like toapologizeto Khelif: \\\"All this controversy certainly made me sad, and I also felt sorry for my opponent, she had nothing to do with it and like me was only here to fight\\u2026 I have nothing against Khelif and on the contrary if I happened to meet her again I would give her a hug.\\\"\", \"from\": 3591, \"to\": 3913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We want to hear it.\", \"from\": 3915, \"to\": 3934, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Send us a tip using our anonymous form.\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 3974, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rolling Stone is a part of Penske Media Corporation.\", \"from\": 3976, \"to\": 4028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3976, \"end\": 3989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rolling_Stone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.94766684719406e-21, \"text\": \"Rolling Stone\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rolling_Stone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rolling_Stone\"}, {\"begin\": 4003, \"end\": 4015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penske_Media_Corporation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Penske Media\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penske_Media_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penske_Media_Corporation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Rolling Stone, LLC.\", \"from\": 4029, \"to\": 4055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4051, \"end\": 4054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999999292399505, \"rank\": 7.07598984889335e-08, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4056, \"to\": 4076, \"entities\": []}]}"